lead_paragraph: Every morning, Venezuelan archer Elias Malave picks up his old bow, attaches a handful of well-worn arrows to his belt and trains for five hours on an empty field, without a coach.

headline.print_headline: Economic Crisis Pummels Venezuelan Sport, Hinders Olympics Athletes
